title: Youth unemployment rate in Zambia in 2019
summary: Overall Youth unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is roughly constant from 2004 to 2005, slightly decreasing from 2005 to 2008, gradually increasing from 2008 to 2010, slightly decreasing from 2010 to 2012, and lastly roughly constant from 2012 to 2016.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 28.26 was reported at Year 2005
The lowest Youth unemployment rate, of value 16.02 was reported at Year 2008
